Sentencas: Double perovskite-type Sr11Mo4O23 material exhibits unusual structural flexibility and oxygen ion mobility.
Titulo: Preparation and characterization of Ta and monovalent alkali metals (Li, Na, K) co-doping on Sr11Mo4O23 electrolyte for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: X-ray diffraction, scanning electron mi-croscopy and electrochemical impedance spectroscopy are used to investigate the effects of acceptor-type Ta and alkali metals co-doping on phase structural, microstructure and electrical properties of Sr11Mo4O23.

Sentencas: All Sr10.8A0.2Mo3.5Ta0.5O23-delta samples show the same single phases as Sr11Mo4O23 (Fdm space group, JCPDS 27-1441).

Sentencas: Doping Ta element at the B-site of Sr11Mo4O23 can inhibit the phase transition of Sr11Mo4O23 to SrMoO4 so as to improve the structure stability of Sr11Mo4O23.On this basis, doping alkali metal at the A-site further enhances the electrical conductivity of Sr11Mo3.5Ta0.5O23-delta(SMTO).

Sentencas: Among them, Sr10.8K0.2Mo3.5Ta0.5O23-delta (SKMTO) sample has the conductivity of 2.02 x 10-2 S/cm in the air at 800 degrees C, which is similar to 233 % higher than that measured for Sr11Mo4O23.
